Sentencas: The poisoning effect of CO2 on the oxygen surface exchange kinetics of BSCF (Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta) is investigated with a novel pulse isotopic exchange technique.
Titulo: Influence of CO2 on Oxygen Surface Exchange Kinetics of Mixed-Conducting Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ Oxide

Sentencas: The surface exchange rate of BSCF severely decreases after in situ exposure to CO2, which is ascribed to carbonate formation on the material surface.
Titulo: Influence of CO2 on Oxygen Surface Exchange Kinetics of Mixed-Conducting Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ Oxide

Sentencas: The detrimental effect of CO2 starts at a low temperature of 375 degrees C and concentration as low as 1%, and becomes more pronounced at higher temperatures.
Titulo: Influence of CO2 on Oxygen Surface Exchange Kinetics of Mixed-Conducting Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ Oxide

Sentencas: Degradation of the surface exchange kinetics is associated with a rapid loss of oxygen permeation performance of BSCF in CO2.
Titulo: Influence of CO2 on Oxygen Surface Exchange Kinetics of Mixed-Conducting Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ Oxide
